# Wellfound Internships – Complete Guide 2026

This guide is for Indian students and recent graduates using Wellfound (previously AngelList Talent) to find internships in 2026.

It is intended for:
- School students in 11th and 12th exploring early startup exposure
- First- and second-year college students with limited or no experience
- Third- and fourth-year undergraduates seeking hands-on tech or startup roles
- Final-year students, postgraduates, and gap-year candidates targeting startup internships with responsibility, equity potential, or conversion to full-time

Wellfound is a global platform connecting job seekers with startups and tech companies. In India, it focuses on tech, software, product, marketing, and early-stage opportunities, often remote or hybrid. As of early March 2026, it features hundreds of active listings in India (including internships), with many from early-stage to growing startups. Remote roles make it accessible for students in tier-2/3 cities like Shirpur, Maharashtra.

Wellfound stands out for startup-minded candidates: roles often involve founding-team work, real impact, and sometimes equity. It suits those preferring dynamic environments over structured corporate internships.

## 1. Current Landscape on Wellfound (March 2026)

Wellfound lists tech and startup opportunities, with a strong emphasis on India-based or remote-eligible roles.

Key observations in early 2026:
- Active roles in India: hundreds to low thousands (fluctuates; strong in software/web development, data, product)
- Remote/work-from-home options: common, especially for internships
- High-demand categories:
  - Software Development / Full Stack / MERN / Backend
  - Web Development / Frontend
  - Data Engineering / Analytics basics
  - Product Management / Operations
  - Digital Marketing / Graphic Design / Content
  - QA / Testing / Automation
- Stipend range: ₹5,000–₹25,000+ per month common; some offer equity or performance bonuses; higher in funded startups
- Internship types: many "founding team" or early-stage, with real responsibilities and potential for extension to full-time

Wellfound is ideal for building startup experience, networking with founders, and accessing roles not heavily advertised on mainstream platforms.

## 2. Eligibility – Who Can Apply

Wellfound has low formal barriers, but competition favors candidates with some skills or projects.

Eligible candidates include:
- 11th/12th students (mainly content, design, or basic tech support via remote roles)
- First- and second-year undergraduates (entry-level startup tasks, learning-focused)
- Third- and fourth-year students (B.Tech CSE/IT, BCA, etc., for dev/product roles)
- Final-year and postgraduate students (stronger fit for technical or founding-team positions)
- Students with backlogs or gaps (highlight skills/projects; be transparent if asked)
- Students from smaller towns – remote filters eliminate location issues

No strict CGPA cutoffs in most cases; demonstrated skills (projects, GitHub) matter more.

## 3. Step-by-Step Application Process

### 3.1 Profile Optimization (Essential for Visibility)

A complete profile increases views from founders and recruiters.

Steps:
1. Sign up or update at https://wellfound.com (free for job seekers).
2. Complete sections:
   - Headline: e.g., "Second-Year CSE Student | Seeking Full-Stack Internship | MERN Projects | Remote"
   - Summary: 3–5 sentences on background, skills, and goals
   - Education: college, branch, year, relevant courses
   - Skills: list realistically (e.g., JavaScript, React, Node.js, Python, Canva, Git)
   - Experience/Projects: add college projects, personal apps, hackathons (link GitHub/repo)
   - Resume: upload PDF (keep ATS-friendly)
   - Preferences: select "Internship", "Remote", "India"
3. Add portfolio links (GitHub, personal site, Behance) – critical for tech roles.

Example summary (beginner):
"First-year student from Maharashtra interested in web development and startups. Self-taught HTML/CSS/JavaScript through projects. Built basic responsive sites. Seeking remote internship to contribute code and learn in an early-stage team."

### 3.2 Searching for Internships

Main methods:
1. Go to https://wellfound.com/jobs or /location/india
2. Search keywords: "Internship", "Intern", "SDE Intern", "Founding Team Intern", "Remote India"
3. Apply filters:
   - Location: "Remote" or "India"
   - Role type: Internship
   - Experience: 0–2 years or "Internship"
   - Sort by: Latest or Relevance
4. Browse categories: Software Engineer, Web Developer, Product Management
5. Set alerts: enable notifications for new matches

Many roles allow "Apply" with one profile (no repeated resumes needed).

### 3.3 Applying and Outreach

Applications are straightforward:
- "Apply" button: submit profile/resume; some require short answers
- Customize if prompted: mention why the startup/role interests you (research their product/funding)
- Direct message founders/recruiters: polite, short (e.g., "Interested in your Full-Stack Intern role. Built MERN projects – happy to discuss.")
- Weekly target: 15–30 quality applications + follow relevant startups

For beginners: focus on "0 years exp" or "founding team" tags; highlight self-learning/projects.

### 3.4 Interviews and Follow-Up

Most interviews: video calls with founders or engineers (10–30 minutes).
Common questions:
- Walk through a project/code
- Why startups/this company?
- Availability and commitment
- Basic technical (e.g., explain a component in your project)

Follow up: thank-you note within 24 hours; restate interest.

## 4. Strategies by Experience Level

**Low/No Experience:**
- Target content/design/marketing/ops internships
- Build quick projects (e.g., personal website, Canva work)
- Apply to remote "founding team" roles for learning

**Intermediate:**
- Highlight GitHub/projects
- Target ₹8,000–₹20,000 stipends + equity
- Message founders directly

**Advanced/Final Year:**
- Apply early for summer 2026
- Target technical roles with PPO potential
- Leverage any prior experience for founding-team spots

## 5. Application Tracking

Use a spreadsheet:
- Date applied
- Startup name
- Role
- Stipend/equity mentioned
- Application method
- Status
- Follow-up date
- Notes

## 6. Common Reasons for Low Response

- Incomplete profile (no projects/links)
- Generic applications
- No customization/research
- Applying only to competitive roles
- Ignoring follow-ups

Avoid scams: never pay fees; all legitimate postings are free.

## 7. Timing and Location Notes

- Early 2026: summer internships rolling out
- Peak: February–May for summer roles
- Shirpur/Maharashtra: use "Remote" filter; many India listings are fully remote

## 8. Comparison to Other Platforms

- Internshala: high-volume student roles, custom questions
- LinkedIn: networking, big brands, referrals
- Wellfound: startup focus, early responsibility, equity, founder access

Many students use all three for maximum coverage.

All information current as of March 2026.

Good luck with your applications.
